Class VectorElementClickInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.carto.ui.VectorElementClickInfo

  • public class VectorElementClickInfo
extends java.lang.Object
    A container class that provides information about a click performed on
    a vector element.

      • VectorElementClickInfo

        public VectorElementClickInfo(ClickType clickType,
                              MapPos clickPos,
                              MapPos elementClickPos,
                              VectorElement vectorElement,
                              Layer layer)
        Constructs a VectorElementClickInfo object from a click position and a vector element.
        Parameters:
        clickType - The click type (SINGLE, DUAL, etc)
        clickPos - The click position in the coordinate system of the base projection.
        elementClickPos - The click position in the coordinate system of the base projection that corresponds to element point.
        vectorElement - The vector element on which the click was performed.
        layer - The layer of the vector element on which the click was performed.

        Returns the position on the clicked element, that is close to the click position.
        For points it will always be the center position, for lines it will be the closest point

        getClickPos().
